http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Directive-on-poll-duty-exemption/article14011897.ece

The State Election Commission has issued orders that women government employees who have children below the age of two years be exempted from election-related duties during conduct of elections to local bodies.The SEC has issued this order following a recommendation from the Commission for the Protection of Child Rights.The Child Rights Commission had pointed out that children below two years of age require the physical presence and care of the mother and this is also the period when they are breastfed. Separating mothers from their children at this age will not be to their best interests, the Commission had recommended to the SEC.The SEC has made it clear in its directive that when orders regarding elections to local bodies are issued, the recommendation of the Child Rights Commission be followed strictly.